    "summary": "TheTVDB exposes two documented REST APIs for developers: a legacy v3 HTTP API at `https://api.thetvdb.com` and a current v4 HTTP API at `https://api4.thetvdb.com/v4`; both require authentication via login-issued bearer/JWT tokens backed by TheTVDB-issued keys.",
    "description": "TheTVDB is a community-maintained database of TV, movie, and related entertainment metadata, including series, episodes, artwork, people, awards, and translations. It offers licensed and user-supported access to that metadata through its public APIs.",
    "credentials": {
      "tvdb_v4_api_key": {
        "type": "api_key",
        "label": "TheTVDB v4 API key",
        "generateUrl": "https://thetvdb.com/dashboard/account/apikey",
        "setup": "Create or log into your TheTVDB account, then open the [API Keys dashboard](https://thetvdb.com/dashboard/account/apikey). To create a v4 key, follow the steps described in [How can I apply for a v4 API key?](https://support.thetvdb.com/kb/faq.php?id=81): Dashboard → Account → **API Keys** → **Create a v4 API Key**, choose either **End-User Subscriptions** or **Negotiated Contract**, agree to the terms, and submit. The support article notes that **End-User Subscriptions** keys are automatically approved, while **Negotiated Contract** keys remain inactive until approved. The public signup page is [API sign up](https://www.thetvdb.com/api-information/signup).",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "tvdb_subscriber_pin": {
        "type": "api_key",
        "label": "TheTVDB subscriber PIN",
        "generateUrl": "https://www.thetvdb.com/subscribe",
        "setup": "Subscribe via the [TheTVDB subscription page](https://www.thetvdb.com/subscribe) while logged in to a TheTVDB account. The [User Subscriptions](https://support.thetvdb.com/kb/faq.php?id=82) article says your subscription immediately provides a unique subscriber `PIN`, visible under Dashboard → **Subscription**. This PIN is global to your user account and can be used with user-supported v4 project keys.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "tvdb_v3_account_identifier": {
        "type": "api_key",
        "label": "TheTVDB v3 account identifier (userkey)",
        "setup": "For v3 `/user` routes only, the v3 API documentation says you must include your TheTVDB account credentials when calling `POST /login`: JSON fields `username` and `userkey`. The same docs say the user's key is labeled `Account Identifier` in the account section of the main site. Obtain it from your TheTVDB account dashboard/account area after signing in.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "tvdb_v3_jwt": {
        "type": "jwt",
        "label": "TheTVDB v3 session JWT",
        "setup": "Use the v3 API `POST /login` endpoint with your legacy v3 API key, and for `/user` routes also include your `username` and `userkey`, as described in the [TheTVDB API v3 spec](https://api.apis.guru/v2/specs/thetvdb.com/3.0.0/swagger.json). The response returns a JWT token. Send it on subsequent requests as `Authorization: Bearer <token>`. The v3 docs say the token expires after 24 hours and can be extended with `GET /refresh_token`.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "tvdb_v4_bearer": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "TheTVDB v4 bearer token",
        "setup": "Call the v4 API `POST /login` with JSON containing your v4 project API key as `apikey`; if the key uses the user-supported model, also include your subscriber `pin`. The v4 docs at [TVDB API V4](https://thetvdb.github.io/v4-api/) and the machine-readable spec [swagger.yml](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/thetvdb/v4-api/main/docs/swagger.yml) state the response returns a bearer token valid for one month. Use it in `Authorization: Bearer <token>` for subsequent API requests.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      }
    },
